    "content": "Within this sturdy, corrosion-resistant polyhedron is [b][i]a phial of ooze acid[/i][/b]; a caustic substance with remarkablepowers of biological alteration.\r\n\r\n[b][i]Caustic Calamity. [/i][/b]As an action, you can press a button on the polyhedron, crushing the phial, and then toss the device up to [b]60 feet[/b] away. The resulting chemical reaction produces an explosion of acid in a [b]20-foot radius[/b]. Each creature in the area must make a[b] DC 16 Dexterity saving throw[/b], taking [b]4d6[/b] acid damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. In addition, the reaction produces unpredictable biomantic effects on a failed saving throw. Roll a [b]2[/b][b]d10[/b] and consult the table below to determine the two effects, ignoring any duplicate results. If a creature comes under an effect lasting [b]1 minute[/b], it can make a [b]DC 16 Constitution saving throw[/b] at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success.\r\n\r\n[table][tr][td][b]d10[/b][/td]\r\n[td][b]Effect[/b][/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr][td][b]1[/b][/td]\r\n[td]The acid stops regeneration and healing. The creature\r\ncan’t regain hit points for [b]1 minute[/b].[/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr][td][b]2[/b][/td]\r\n[td]The acid coats creatures, dissolving them. The\r\ncreature takes [b]2d6[/b] acid damage at the start of each\r\nof its turns for [b]1 minute[/b].[/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr][td][b]3[/b][/td]\r\n[td]Parts of creatures’ bodies meld together. The creature\r\nhas [b]disadvantage [/b]on attack rolls for [b]1 minute[/b].[/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr][td][b]4[/b][/td]\r\n[td]The acid fuses feet and footwear to the ground. The\r\ncreature is [b]restrained[/b] until the end of your next turn.[/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr][td][b]5[/b][/td]\r\n[td]The acid fuses the eyelids shut. The creature is\r\n[b]blinded [/b]until the end of your next turn.[/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr][td][b]6[/b][/td]\r\n[td]The acid causes creatures’ skin to become phosphorescent.\r\nThe creature is under the effect of the\r\n[i]faerie fire [/i]spell for [b]1 minute[/b].[/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr][td][b]7[/b][/td]\r\n[td]The acid causes growths to appear and disappear\r\non creatures’ bodies, hindering their actions. The\r\ncreature is under the effect of the [i]bane[/i] spell for [b]1[/b]\r\n[b]minute[/b].[/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr][td][b]8[/b][/td]\r\n[td]The acid causes creatures to shrink. The creature is\r\nunder the reduce effect of the [i]enlarge/reduce[/i] spell\r\nfor [b]1 minute[/b].[/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr][td][b]9[/b][/td]\r\n[td]The acid fuses mouths shut. The creature is under\r\nthe effect of the @[zippit!](spell:f07ce072-7bc2-43d4-9430-d47e53e81ed2) spell for 1 minute.[/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr][td][b]10[/b][/td]\r\n[td]Roll twice on the table, rerolling any further 10s\r\nand duplicate results.[/td]\r\n[/tr][/table]\r\nOnce this property of the item has been used, it can’t be used again until the next dawn and a new [i]phial of ooze acid[/i] has been installed in the device.\r\n\r\n[b][i]Trigger Warning. [/i][/b]Instead of throwing the bomb, you can use an action to plant it on a surface and set it to detonate in a specific situation. As an action, a creature can disarm a bomb set to explode in this way with a successful [b]DC 16 Dexterity (Sleight of Hand)[/b] check. On a failed check, the bomb goes off and the creature that made the check automatically fails the saving throw. Choose one of the following detonation options:\r\n[ul]\r\n[li][b]Proximity Trigger.[/b] Choose a range between 0 and 20 feet. The first Small or larger creature to move within that distance of the bomb after you leave the area sets it off. A creature that succeeds on a [b]DC 16 Dexterity (Stealth)[/b] check can approach the bomb without triggering it.[/li]\r\n[li][b]Time Bomb.[/b] Choose an amount of time ranging from 1 to 100 rounds. On initiative count 20 of the round you choose, the bomb explodes.[/li]\r\n[/ul]",
